Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.43,0:00:18.40,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.89,0:01:48.82,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 09 - The Road to Adelaide
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.54,0:02:17.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go! Go! Down!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.15,0:02:20.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go. Behave yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.70,0:02:23.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.95,0:02:24.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Need your help!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.74,0:02:25.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.28,0:02:32.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.17,0:02:33.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.37,0:02:46.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And down!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.89,0:02:49.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All right, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.11,0:02:56.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how many more people have come\Non that ship that arrived yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.60,0:03:00.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very big ship, so it can probably carry \Nup to 100 passengers on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.59,0:03:04.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Someone else would probably be living here, \Non our spot, in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.33,0:03:05.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.65,0:03:07.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone needs help over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.40,0:03:08.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, all is good here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.53,0:03:10.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, Ben is apparently coming late.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.46,0:03:13.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose the cart's owner \Nhadn't quite sobered up yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.90,0:03:16.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, you could say he was blind drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.95,0:03:21.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do we really have to trust someone so unreliable \Nwith transporting our precious furniture?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.90,0:03:24.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're not trusting Mr. Bard to do it all by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.57,0:03:26.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The three of us will be accompanying him. {him, wife and tob}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.91,0:03:31.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bard, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.75,0:03:34.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like that! Keep walking, you slacker! {/walk fast/steadily}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.79,0:03:35.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:37.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Much obliged for what you did. {/for meeting me/for that}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:40.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, the soil here is sandy and soft, \Nso my cart's wheels are prone to sinking. {何しろ下が砂地でやわらかいから車輪がめり込むんでな}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.75,0:03:41.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:51.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Good morning, Mr. Jamling!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.06,0:03:55.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Ben. Aren't you glad \Nyou'll be going to Adelaide under a fine weather?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.33,0:03:57.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Is your leg doing better today?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.09,0:04:00.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for asking. \NIt's the same as yesterday, still hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.52,0:04:01.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please take care, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.26,0:04:03.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.30,0:04:04.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.73,0:04:10.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that ox would still be able to move, \Nonce all their luggage is loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.62,0:04:13.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, what are you mumbling about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.10,0:04:16.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... You know the Popples \Nare moving to Adelaide today, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.00,0:04:17.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you don't feel too lonely without them. {honestly, I don't understand what he means at all: さびしくなるなって 言ってたんだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.98,0:04:20.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, ain't we also going to Adelaide soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.34,0:04:23.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. As soon as this bloody leg recovers, we do. {annoying; infuriating; provoking; irritating; aggravating; vexing}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.50,0:04:25.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.19,0:04:34.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We were wrong! On that raft, \Nit's not people they're bringing. It's sheep! Sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.02,0:04:39.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! So many sheep, \Nand they all came from England?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.97,0:04:43.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we can keep sheep in Australia, \Nit's bound to become a mighty fancy place!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.82,0:04:51.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You think that ship could've \Nbrought here oxen and horses, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.02,0:04:54.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way I would know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.26,0:04:58.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we'd have enough oxen and horses here, \Ntransporting our luggage would be a cakewalk!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:01.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And dad could live in our prefabricated home, \Ninstead of selling it. {unsure what's sunda here tbh}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.39,0:05:06.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But isn't it nice that instead of a prefabricated home, \Nhe bought us another house in Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.30,0:05:10.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear what Ben said? \NHe wouldn't exactly call it a house, even.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.87,0:05:13.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"Shack" seems like way more fitting a word. {/if you say cabin, that'd be a perfect description}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.12,0:05:15.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll be sleeping in a shack \Nwhen we get to Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.72,0:05:18.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no telling if we'll even be able to sleep in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.48,0:05:19.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.42,0:05:22.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, that shack has no more than two rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.26,0:05:23.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Only two?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:26.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, the two of us \Nwill keep sleeping in a barrel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.84,0:05:29.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it would at least be a decent barrel. {/in good condition}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.77,0:05:35.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.69,0:05:41.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate! Whatcha people doin' all the way out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.90,0:05:44.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to watch them \Nunload the sheep from the ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.06,0:06:16.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right. Folks from your family \Nhave been looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.70,0:06:17.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:19.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, they're done \Nloading the luggage onto the cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:23.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, we need to return quickly! Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.31,0:06:27.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Sister, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.13,0:06:33.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And like this! Looks good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.20,0:06:37.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben stays behind for now. \NWe don't want to leave our things unattended.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.30,0:06:40.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Well, I have to travel \Nback and forth a lot, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:44.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,so there's no way I could look after your furniture all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.15,0:06:45.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.23,0:06:49.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Once we hire another cart in Adelaide, \Nwe'll come back for this furniture. {sounds a bit irresponsible of him to leave son behind while they haven't even found that cart yet but apparently that's exactly what he's saying: アデレードで 荷車の手配ができたらこの家具を取りに来るからな}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.31,0:06:50.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.22,0:06:54.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll try to find a cart as soon as possible, \Nhowever, I can't tell if it won't take us up to a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.63,0:06:57.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It ain't easy to find a cart these days!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.18,0:07:01.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even I myself will have to switch \Nto working without day-offs, starting tomorrow. {unsure what he means, probably needs the ox to plow the field or idk? 俺だってあしたからは1日も休みなしで仕事が入ってるんだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.33,0:07:02.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm so fed up with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:06.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you'll be able to find a wagon around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:11.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like, if they decide to send something here \Nfrom Adelaide, and the cart would be returning empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.34,0:07:14.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, Mr. Parker, I'd like to ask you \Nto help Ben with loading this. { to load (luggage); to carry; to take on board​esp. 載せる}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:17.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be sure to compensate you \Nfor all the trouble. {no clue what he means: 金は私の方で払う形にして}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.16,0:07:18.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, will do just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.98,0:07:21.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which reminds me, Ben, \Nwhere are you going to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.33,0:07:22.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In this barrel, I suppose.{/will sleep}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.79,0:07:25.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind you coming to my tent to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.25,0:07:28.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That tent is obviously too spacious for me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.46,0:07:31.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Although I feel bad, \Nasking you for so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:35.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing. These new lands necessitate \Nincreased responsiveness towards one another. {lit: in this new land, starting now, we need to help}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.78,0:07:37.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.10,0:07:40.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, I entrust Ben \Nand this luggage into your care.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.18,0:07:40.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.47,0:07:43.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But now, it's time to hit the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.27,0:07:44.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.30,0:07:47.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Kate and Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.98,0:07:50.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. They've just returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.58,0:07:57.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right. The ship that brought us all here\Nwill be returning to England today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.19,0:08:02.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I thought so. Probably, only to return here \Nsome half a year later, carrying even more immigrants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.61,0:08:03.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.79,0:08:07.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why John didn't come to see us off? {VERY unsure what she means, could be "john might not make it in time to come on that one"; ジヨンはそれで来られなかったのよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.35,0:08:08.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.10,0:08:14.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I was already considering \Nleaving you two here. {お前たちをここへ置いていこうとしてたんだぞ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.69,0:08:17.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No way! {/That's a lie!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.70,0:08:31.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Keep walking, you slacker!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.80,0:08:38.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The ship that came yesterday \Nbrought over a whole lotta sheep!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.14,0:08:40.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The shore was filled completely with just sheep!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.63,0:08:41.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're exaggerating. {unsure what he means by オーバー}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.87,0:08:43.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's the truth! Right, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:46.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I felt so bad for the sheep that fell into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.32,0:08:49.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Its fur was soaking up the water rapidly \Nand I thought it'd drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.29,0:08:52.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think of it, wasn't there a shepherd with sheep near Adelaide, too, dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.82,0:08:55.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Ah, Ben, you should return now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.51,0:08:57.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we walk together just a little more...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.41,0:08:59.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, up to here is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.16,0:09:00.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bard! A quick stop, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.92,0:09:02.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.65,0:09:06.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.75,0:09:07.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.29,0:09:11.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll try to come pick up \Nthe rest of our stuff as soon as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:12.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.67,0:09:15.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Jamling promised \Nto share their bread with you. {lit is "share the bread with ..." but it's not like he has the bread and jamlings dont? or is it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.28,0:09:17.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.58,0:09:21.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good, but we have to go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.40,0:09:22.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bard!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.72,0:09:23.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.41,0:09:27.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! We're leaving, you slacker!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.14,0:09:28.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.56,0:09:30.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.38,0:09:38.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Take care, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.66,0:09:42.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.45,0:09:44.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And you two, walk straight all the way to Adelaide. {unusre what he means, maybe "don't slack off while walking" but I already used slacker for the ox}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.43,0:09:45.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.42,0:09:51.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to go to the shore \Nto see the sheep, brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.83,0:09:54.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go see them! \NAnd you walk straight, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.40,0:09:55.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.30,0:10:06.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good! Keep going, you slacker! There!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.35,0:10:07.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.40,0:10:11.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.04,0:10:21.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John's ship is still here, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.03,0:10:22.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.83,0:10:29.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara! Do what I told you last night\Nand go ahead, with those two in tow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.74,0:10:30.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.30,0:10:34.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's a shame you didn't get to see John once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:36.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I saw him yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.38,0:10:40.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Kate and Lucy-May, \Nwe three need to go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:41.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.71,0:10:43.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait for me, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.20,0:10:45.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, you need to walk faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.10,0:10:47.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't keep up,\Nwe'll have to leave you behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.75,0:10:48.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.19,0:11:00.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! Walk faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.22,0:11:07.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.78,0:11:11.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:15.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, did you notice? \NA mighty strange lizard right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.25,0:11:18.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A lizard? I'm not very fond of lizards, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.72,0:11:22.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But this one is nothing like what I've seen before! \NYou should come see it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.29,0:11:46.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my. And which way is his head?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.56,0:11:48.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll know when it moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.25,0:12:11.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.21,0:12:13.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Told you! A mighty funny thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.75,0:12:16.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, it's very funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.11,0:12:17.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Grrr...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.66,0:12:18.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.50,0:12:21.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.20,0:12:22.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.40,0:12:23.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.56,0:12:28.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not make any more detours than that, Lucy-may.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.45,0:12:30.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.75,0:12:54.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.44,0:13:16.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All right, doctor, we've here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.35,0:13:16.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.44,0:13:18.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.04,0:13:19.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.48,0:13:22.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Down I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.35,0:13:23.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:27.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ben. Glad to see you. \NThis means your family hadn't left yet, had it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.73,0:13:30.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm the only one left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.05,0:13:31.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone else left for Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.89,0:13:33.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Had it been long already? {/long time ago?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.76,0:13:35.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, not particularly long...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.25,0:13:39.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, John, I'm going on ahead \Nto Mr. Jamling's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.94,0:13:43.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. Just one thing, doctor. \NMake sure to come back in an hour, alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.56,0:13:47.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you do it leisurely, in your usual manner, \Nthe ship will leave without you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.26,0:13:51.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He-he. Examining Mr. Jamling's leg \Ncannot possibly take an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.85,0:13:56.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Speaking of which, \Nwhich way is Mr. Jamling's tent here, kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.00,0:13:58.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.44,0:14:02.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know. Ben, could you \Naccompany doctor while you're at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.42,0:14:04.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. But doctor seems mighty drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.79,0:14:06.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, like always.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.30,0:14:07.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.55,0:14:08.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.45,0:14:10.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go see Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.99,0:14:14.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,O-ooops.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:20.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness... {なんとまあ}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.60,0:14:40.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like that! Don't stop walking, you slacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.04,0:14:41.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.02,0:14:50.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara's group must already be far ahead, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.90,0:14:55.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, however, she is with the little ones,\Nso I doubt they can walk very fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.34,0:14:56.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.66,0:14:58.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.61,0:15:00.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Someone called you just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.16,0:15:00.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.17,0:15:04.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.31,0:15:07.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's John!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.38,0:15:09.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,His ship hadn't set sail yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.12,0:15:17.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I caught up with you sooner than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.08,0:15:19.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I heard your ship is about to depart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.63,0:15:20.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.01,0:15:21.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.01,0:15:25.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I still have a little more time until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.40,0:15:27.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And... Where is Clara?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.38,0:15:30.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara went ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.36,0:15:32.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.74,0:15:37.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. With Kate and Lucy-May in tow, \Nwe sent her ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.24,0:15:39.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The cart cannot go faster than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.23,0:15:41.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but... was it long ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.52,0:15:46.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember for certain, \Nbut I don't think they're that terribly far yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.44,0:15:47.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.46,0:15:50.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? But do you really have the time for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:52.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I still have about 40 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.15,0:15:53.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just 40 minutes, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.47,0:15:56.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In either case, I'll try to catch up. Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.20,0:16:05.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Ouch! Ouch! Ouch. \NHurts terribly there, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.65,0:16:06.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.64,0:16:11.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The recovery is slower than I anticipated. \NCould it be that there's a bone fracture, after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.78,0:16:15.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be, doc! \NDidn't you tell me it's a mere sprain the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.72,0:16:18.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But in that case, the swelling \Nwould've receded already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.70,0:16:19.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Does it hurt here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.83,0:16:24.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Doctor! Have you decided to kill me today? {korosu ki ka?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.17,0:16:28.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,W-wait, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.62,0:16:32.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whiskey, sir. Helps numb the pain. {/my painkiller}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.09,0:16:33.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Unacceptable! Totally unacceptable!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.86,0:16:36.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.28,0:16:39.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Drinking things like whiskey \Nwould only do more harm to your leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.70,0:16:41.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.08,0:16:44.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But when drinking this, \NI can at least forget about the throbbing pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.44,0:16:48.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No way! It would only hurt more from drinking whiskey. {hope he means this by wo nomu kara itamu} \NLet me have that for a moment. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.61,0:16:49.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:50.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I said lend me this booze bottle!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:52.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.76,0:16:54.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, don't say more. Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.18,0:17:02.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.20,0:17:03.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.14,0:17:05.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't drink that. It's a bit too tasty! {これはいけない ちよつとうますぎる\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.64,0:17:06.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.27,0:17:15.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh... This stuff is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.13,0:17:17.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No way you can drink something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.64,0:17:27.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys sure have loaded \Na ton and a little extra onto their cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.12,0:17:30.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They're lucky to have managed \Nto hire two oxcarts at once. {unsure what exactly she wants to say}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:32.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Must be someone with very deep pockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.11,0:17:33.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it Mr. Pettywell over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.69,0:17:34.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.32,0:17:38.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and that looks like Mr. Pettywell's wife, \Nalways in her ritzy feather hat. {unsure what she means by "to be affected; to put on airs hat"; ほら ペティウェルさんの奥さんの気どった羽根帽子が見えるじゃない }
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.12,0:17:45.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And it's their servants, \Nwho are pushing the carts from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.01,0:17:51.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But then, sis, in this mountain of stuff, loaded onto two carts, there must be our prefabricated home, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.49,0:17:54.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not exactly "ours" anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.84,0:17:57.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, dad couldn't help \Nbut to sell it to Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.01,0:18:01.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I bet the prefabricated home is loaded \Nonto the right cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.62,0:18:05.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's loaded onto the left one as well. \NOne cart can't hold all of it. {/won't be enough to fit ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.82,0:18:06.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.09,0:18:09.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear what I said? You!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.20,0:18:11.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They're quarreling over something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.06,0:18:12.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get closer to find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.90,0:18:14.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be running!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.37,0:18:20.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I won't tolerate any back talk \Nfrom just some handymen for hire! {lit: person working for me}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.62,0:18:22.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But sir, you're asking for impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.98,0:18:26.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Going any faster than that \Nis totally, decisively, impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.56,0:18:31.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to get to Adelaide sooner! That's exactly \Nwhy I paid you more than double the usual fee!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.51,0:18:34.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you two! You'd better do as master says, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.62,0:18:36.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.06,0:18:38.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Especially when we're so ridiculously overburdened!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.51,0:18:41.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we speed up any more than that, \Nthe ox would drop dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.64,0:18:43.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't care less if the ox dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.68,0:18:44.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my! How cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:47.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If the ox dies, who'll be transporting your things?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.93,0:18:49.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why am I supposed to think of that? {honestly no clue what he means: そんなこと知るもんか - probably rather "I don't know/haven't thought about that}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.48,0:18:54.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All I want is just for you rascals to transport \Nmy prefabricated home and furniture already!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.52,0:18:56.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And we're doing just that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:57.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do it faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.32,0:18:59.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's being a lunatic again. Let's go now. {absurd; ridiculous; silly; ludicrous; nonsensical; asinine; foolish​}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.29,0:19:04.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you rascals don't start going faster than that, \NI'll have you return half of the money to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.94,0:19:06.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right! You'll return half of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.70,0:19:07.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Want half of it back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.95,0:19:10.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How are you better than a simple thief, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:13.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What? Thief? When did I ever do any thievery?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.32,0:19:16.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell sure is capricious, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.28,0:19:17.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That, too, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.57,0:19:20.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He just thinks the power of money \Ncan get him anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.45,0:19:23.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He sure does! \NLike he got our prefabricated home! {actually just "aaah"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.50,0:19:25.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, it's not "ours" anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.46,0:19:26.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They're throwing fists now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.60,0:19:28.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Apologize, I said! \NWhen did I do any thievery?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.98,0:19:30.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Apologize to the master, you! {does "the" here add a certain respect?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.39,0:19:31.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of me! {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.20,0:19:32.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.95,0:19:34.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, to think they call themselves grown-ups... {this SWS wording is surprisingly good enough}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.92,0:19:36.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell just punched him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.68,0:19:38.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Now he's been punched back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.24,0:19:39.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's overwhelmed! {unsure, "to be overturned; to be reversed; to turn over; to capsize" could be "thrown on the ground" or somethingg}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.63,0:19:42.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just what's gotten into those people?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:43.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.82,0:19:44.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.57,0:19:45.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:45.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Swindler! {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.61,0:19:47.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you punch me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.74,0:19:49.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not letting is slide now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.19,0:19:52.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.65,0:19:53.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's too soon for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.99,0:19:57.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, sis, why don't we just eat our lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.80,0:20:00.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're still not even halfway there. {/haven't walked half}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.17,0:20:01.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm very hungry already!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.37,0:20:05.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For a moment, hush, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.91,0:20:07.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.66,0:20:11.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though somebody \Nwas calling out my name just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.03,0:20:15.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of this forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.47,0:20:21.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps I just imagined it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.93,0:20:22.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.72,0:20:23.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.83,0:20:27.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.99,0:20:28.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They're calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.47,0:20:31.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right? You heard it too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.04,0:20:35.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Was it John?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.26,0:20:38.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's wrong, sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.81,0:20:40.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John is calling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.51,0:20:41.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To where? {unsure, could be "from where?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.44,0:20:43.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The ship's supposed to set sail today. {actually just "we were told the ship departs"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.10,0:20:46.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He came to see me before leaving. {added}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.93,0:20:48.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.56,0:20:52.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.02,0:20:54.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It really was John all along, sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.20,0:20:55.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my! John!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.81,0:20:57.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.20,0:21:03.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we leave them alone for a bit? {to step aside; to move (i.e. out of the way); to make way​}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.69,0:21:05.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like a sound thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.69,0:21:06.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.04,0:21:11.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.54,0:21:17.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Made it... {/I caught up to you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.46,0:21:19.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought we'd never meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.94,0:21:20.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We did... {/I saw you}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.71,0:21:21.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still have time?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.76,0:21:22.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.96,0:21:23.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.76,0:21:25.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No time at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.03,0:21:26.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.70,0:21:28.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to see you one last time... {/even if with just one eye/a glance}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.90,0:21:32.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad I got to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.97,0:21:34.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And on that, goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.08,0:21:36.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.02,0:21:39.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, and wait for me. \NI will definitely come again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.02,0:21:39.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.73,0:21:47.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, John!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.17,0:22:05.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get to see her, John?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.39,0:22:07.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I saw her!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.39,0:22:10.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And take care, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.15,0:22:11.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You take care, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.10,0:22:18.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He took the trouble to come, \Neven knowing he's out of time. {unsure what he means, probably "did the impossible and came" or "forced himself to come"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.73,0:22:20.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.37,0:22:50.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Dayton!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.65,0:22:54.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Dayton!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.60,0:22:56.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Dayton!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.10,0:22:57.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.27,0:23:01.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for Dr. Dayton,\Nhe returned a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.41,0:23:03.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,With my whiskey under his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.94,0:23:05.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.76,0:23:18.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Dayton!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.21,0:23:21.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Dayton!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:37.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister was glowing with happiness \Nfrom that unexpected encounter with John.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.58,0:23:42.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it even charged me and Lucy-May with delight, \Nmaking our gait much lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.95,0:23:46.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Once we're out of the woods, we're in Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.50,0:24:06.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By mistake, we walked the wrong road \Non our way to Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.92,0:24:11.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Some animal was chasing us three \Nall the way through the forest. {unsure why she says mori no naka if they are apparently in the field already}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.59,0:24:15.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"The City of Greenery".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.16,0:24:16.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
